"{\"24\":\"But since you rejected me when I called and no one gave heed when I stretched out my hand,\",\"25\":\"since you ignored all my advice and would not accept my rebuke,\",\"26\":\"I in turn will laugh at your disaster; I will mock when calamity overtakes you-\",\"27\":\"when calamity overtakes you like a storm, when disaster sweeps over you like a whirlwind, when distress and trouble overwhelm you.\",\"20\":\"Wisdom calls aloud in the street, she raises her voice in the public squares;\",\"21\":\"at the head of the noisy streets she cries out, in the gateways of the city she makes her speech:\",\"22\":\"\\\"How long will you simple ones love your simple ways? How long will mockers delight in mockery and fools hate knowledge?\",\"23\":\"If you had responded to my rebuke, I would have poured out my heart to you and made my thoughts known to you.\",\"28\":\"\\\"Then they will call to me but I will not answer; they will look for me but will not find me.\",\"29\":\"Since they hated knowledge and did not choose to fear the LORD,\",\"1\":\"The proverbs of Solomon son of David, king of Israel:\",\"3\":\"for acquiring a disciplined and prudent life, doing what is right and just and fair;\",\"2\":\"for attaining wisdom and discipline; for understanding words of insight;\",\"5\":\"let the wise listen and add to their learning, and let the discerning get guidance-\",\"4\":\"for giving prudence to the simple, knowledge and discretion to the young-\",\"7\":\"The fear of the Lord is the beginning of knowledge, but fools despise wisdom and discipline.\",\"6\":\"for understanding proverbs and parables, the sayings and riddles of the wise.\",\"9\":\"They will be a garland to grace your head and a chain to adorn your neck.\",\"8\":\"Listen, my son, to your father's instruction and do not forsake your mother's teaching.\",\"11\":\"If they say, \\\"Come along with us; let's lie in wait for someone's blood, let's waylay some harmless soul;\",\"10\":\"My son, if sinners entice you, do not give in to them.\",\"13\":\"we will get all sorts of valuable things and fill our houses with plunder;\",\"12\":\"let's swallow them alive, like the grave, and whole, like those who go down to the pit;\",\"15\":\"my son, do not go along with them, do not set foot on their paths;\",\"14\":\"throw in your lot with us, and we will share a common purse\\\"-\",\"17\":\"How useless to spread a net in full view of all the birds!\",\"16\":\"for their feet rush into sin, they are swift to shed blood.\",\"19\":\"Such is the end of all who go after ill-gotten gain; it takes away the lives of those who get it.\",\"18\":\"These men lie in wait for their own blood; they waylay only themselves!\",\"31\":\"they will eat the fruit of their ways and be filled with the fruit of their schemes.\",\"30\":\"since they would not accept my advice and spurned my rebuke,\",\"33\":\"but whoever listens to me will live in safety and be at ease, without fear of harm.\\\"\",\"32\":\"For the waywardness of the simple will kill them, and the complacency of fools will destroy them;\"}"